---
metadata: {
    partial_name: 'Ecommerce | Products | Product Tags'
}
---
{% comment %}
    Shared .product-tags badge strip — used by the product list card (product_card)
    and the product detail page (detail), so the tag rules stay identical.

    IMPORTANT: pass the tag array as `tags`, NOT `product_tags`. A param whose name
    matches the partial's own filename gets clobbered (it arrives empty) — that's why
    the first shared-partial attempt failed. The working shared partials confirm the
    rule: star_rating takes `rating`, tag_chip takes `tag` — param name != partial name.

    Caps the strip at two badges, highest priority first, to avoid a noisy stack:
    Sale > Bestseller > New Arrival > Staff Pick > Limited.
    Pass 1 walks the priority order: "Sale" (#1) matches ANY tag containing the word
    "sale" (e.g. "20% sale") and keeps that custom label; the rest match exactly and
    render the canonical label. Tags are database-driven, so Pass 2 fills any remaining
    slot with the product's other tags in their stored order. Rendered tags are tracked
    by index so none renders twice.

    Params:
    - tags : array of tag label strings (from the product's custom fields)
{% endcomment %}
{%- if tags and tags.size > 0 -%}
    {%- assign tag_priority = 'Sale,Bestseller,New Arrival,Staff Pick,Limited' | split: ',' -%}
    {%- assign tags_shown = 0 -%}
    {%- assign rendered_idx = '' | split: ',' -%}
    <div class="product-tags">
        {%- for pt in tag_priority -%}
            {%- if tags_shown >= 2 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
            {%- assign pt_norm = pt | downcase | strip -%}
            {%- for tag in tags -%}
                {%- if tags_shown >= 2 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
                {%- assign idx_str = forloop.index0 | append: '' -%}
                {%- unless rendered_idx contains idx_str -%}
                    {%- assign tag_norm = tag | downcase | strip -%}
                    {%- assign is_match = false -%}
                    {%- assign render_label = pt -%}
                    {%- if pt_norm == 'sale' -%}
                        {%- if tag_norm contains 'sale' -%}
                            {%- assign is_match = true -%}
                            {%- assign render_label = tag -%}
                        {%- endif -%}
                    {%- elsif tag_norm == pt_norm -%}
                        {%- assign is_match = true -%}
                    {%- endif -%}
                    {%- if is_match -%}
                        {% include 'modules/ecommerce/products/tag_chip', tag: render_label %}
                        {%- assign tags_shown = tags_shown | plus: 1 -%}
                        {%- assign rendered_idx = rendered_idx | array_add: idx_str -%}
                    {%- endif -%}
                {%- endunless -%}
            {%- endfor -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
        {%- comment -%} Pass 2: fill remaining slots with not-yet-rendered (non-priority) tags in stored order. {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- for tag in tags -%}
            {%- if tags_shown >= 2 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
            {%- assign idx_str = forloop.index0 | append: '' -%}
            {%- unless rendered_idx contains idx_str -%}
                {% include 'modules/ecommerce/products/tag_chip', tag: tag %}
                {%- assign tags_shown = tags_shown | plus: 1 -%}
                {%- assign rendered_idx = rendered_idx | array_add: idx_str -%}
            {%- endunless -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
{%- endif -%}
